{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/libnbd-io_uring-1","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"00d2d5ad-a377-5d84-84bf-00c5c0c14709","html":"<h1 id=\"research-notes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#research-notes\" aria-label=\"research notes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Research Notes</h1>\n<p>This post contains some research notes so don’t expect great quality, this is just to document how I go around devising a solution so you don’t assume me as some systems programming wizard.</p>\n<p>I will merge my notes from earlier in first note and will add dates to later notes.</p>\n<h3 id=\"example-projects\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#example-projects\" aria-label=\"example projects permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Example projects</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wheybags/wcp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">wcp</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"2nd-june-2021\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2nd-june-2021\" aria-label=\"2nd june 2021 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2nd June 2021</h2>\n<h3 id=\"concepts\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#concepts\" aria-label=\"concepts permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Concepts</h3>\n<h4 id=\"libnbd-related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#libnbd-related\" aria-label=\"libnbd related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>libnbd related:</h4>\n<p>2 copies are done during a nbdcopy command one when kernel transfers data to userspace and other when userspace process (nbdcopy) send to the kernel to send it to destination. io<em>uring can help us avoid the second copy which is significant when we look at the _flamegraph</em>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"io_uring-related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#io_uring-related\" aria-label=\"io_uring related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>io_uring related:</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://unixism.net/loti/tutorial/sq_poll.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Submission Queue Polling</a>: A nice feature where kernel threads polls <em>SQEs</em> for you so you don’t have to call <code class=\"language-text\">io_uring_enter(2)</code>, set the flag <code class=\"language-text\">IOURING_SETUP_SQEPOLL</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">io_uring_params</code> when</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://unixism.net/loti/tutorial/link_liburing.html#linking-requests\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Linked Requests</a>: Submission are not processed in order they were submitted, their completion time depends on many different factors but it’s better to assume they are completed in random order. Linked Requests enable us to ensure some requests only start after other are completed.</p>\n<h3 id=\"code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#code\" aria-label=\"code permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Code</h3>\n<p>Using io_uring directly is requires complex boilerplate which though not too difficult but is wasted effort. For this purpose, liburing helps code code is smaller and hence easier to maintain.</p>\n<h4 id=\"liburing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#liburing\" aria-label=\"liburing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>liburing</h4>\n<h5 id=\"setup\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#setup\" aria-label=\"setup permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>setup</h5>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"c\"><pre class=\"language-c\"><code class=\"language-c\"><span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">define</span> <span class=\"token macro-name\">ENTRIES</span> <span class=\"token expression\"><span class=\"token number\">32</span></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">io_uring</span> ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">io_uring_queue_init</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>ENTRIES<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h5 id=\"submission\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#submission\" aria-label=\"submission permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>submission</h5>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"c\"><pre class=\"language-c\"><code class=\"language-c\"><span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">io_uring_sqe</span> sqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">io_uring_cqe</span> cqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* get an sqe and fill in a READV operation */</span>\nsqe <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">io_uring_get_sqe</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">io_uring_prep_readv</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>sqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> fd<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>iovec<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> offset<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* tell the kernel we have an sqe ready for consumption */</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">io_uring_submit</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* wait for the sqe to complete */</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">io_uring_wait_cqe</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>cqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* read and process cqe event */</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">app_handle_cqe</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>cqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">io_uring_cqe_seen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> cqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"iovec\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#iovec\" aria-label=\"iovec permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>iovec</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"c\"><pre class=\"language-c\"><code class=\"language-c\"><span class=\"token keyword\">char</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span>str0 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"hello \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">char</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span>str1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"world\\n\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">iovec</span> iov<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">ssize_t</span> nwritten<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\niov<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>iov_base <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> str0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\niov<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>iov_len <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">strlen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>str0<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\niov<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>iov_base <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> str1<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\niov<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>iov_len <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">strlen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>str1<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nnwritten <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">writev</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>STDOUT_FILENO<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> iov<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"sysconf\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sysconf\" aria-label=\"sysconf permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>sysconf</h4>\n<p>how to determine cache size</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"c\"><pre class=\"language-c\"><code class=\"language-c\"><span class=\"token keyword\">long</span> cache_size <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> _SC_LEVEL2_CACHE_SIZE<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"sample-liburing-program-write-to-file\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sample-liburing-program-write-to-file\" aria-label=\"sample liburing program write to file permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sample liburing program (write to file)</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"c\"><pre class=\"language-c\"><code class=\"language-c\"><span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;liburing.h></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;fcntl.h></span></span>\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;string.h></span></span>\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">include</span> <span class=\"token string\">&lt;unistd.h></span></span>\n<span class=\"token macro property\"><span class=\"token directive-hash\">#</span><span class=\"token directive keyword\">define</span> <span class=\"token macro-name\">QD</span> <span class=\"token expression\"><span class=\"token number\">32</span></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">io_uring</span> ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">io_uring_queue_init</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>QD<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">io_uring_sqe</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span>sqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  sqe <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">io_uring_get_sqe</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">char</span> buff<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">16</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Hello \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"again \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"world!\\n\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> fd <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">creat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"myfile.txt\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> S_IRUSR <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> S_IWUSR<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">iovec</span> iov<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token operator\">++</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    iov<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>iov_base <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> buff<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    iov<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>iov_len <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">strlen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>buff<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">sizeof</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">char</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">io_uring_prep_writev</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>sqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> fd<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> iov<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">io_uring_submit</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">io_uring_cqe</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span>cqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// wait for events to complete</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">io_uring_wait_cqe</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>cqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// mark event as reaped</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">io_uring_cqe_seen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> cqe<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// exit</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">io_uring_queue_exit</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>ring<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token function\">close</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>fd<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/libnbd-io_uring-1","tagSlugs":["/tag/libnbd/","/tag/iouring/","/tag/systems-programming/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-06-01T19:12+00:00","description":"io_uring is the new and better way to do asynchronus I/O on linux, tag along with me on a journey to learn it by doing, on a real life project libnbd!","tags":["libnbd","iouring","systems-programming"],"title":"Accelerating libnbd on linux using io_uring [1]","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/blog/static/967f078a7efde66caf23dac6fb3b0b67/io_uring-sq-cq.png"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/libnbd-io_uring-1"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}